{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Normal Rotate"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 23], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [149, 232], "text": [" Rotates a Normal Map while correcting recalculating it\u2019s internal vectors "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [232, 476], "text": ["A traditional Xform is not the correct way of rotating a normal map. Because a normal map represents directions and not colors, the red/green/blue channels always need to be the correct representation of the Tangent, Binormal and Normal Axis."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [482, 532], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/movies/rotate_xform.gif", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/movies/rotate_xform.gif"}]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [532, 569], "text": ["XForm rotating a Normal Map"]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [476, 482], "container": true, "type": "col"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [575, 626], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/movies/rotate_normal.gif", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/movies/rotate_normal.gif"}]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [626, 671], "text": ["Normal Rotate rotating a Normal Map"]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [569, 575], "container": true, "type": "col"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "col_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [671, 801], "text": ["Isolating only the green channel will be a better way to see what is happening. Ignore the background issues on the Xform node. "]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [807, 863], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/movies/rotate_xform_green.gif", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/movies/rotate_xform_green.gif"}]}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [863, 900], "text": ["XForm rotating a Normal Map"]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [801, 807], "container": true, "type": "co